OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1778529954
OL,3,CHow could Keir Starmer be replaced and
OL,4,Cwhat would be the next steps?
OL,6,FWes Streeting so far has been
OL,7,Freluctant to make the first move.
OL,8,FAngela Rayner has needed more time to
OL,9,Fsort out her tax affairs and the
OL,10,Fcontender who polls best amongst the
OL,11,Fpublic, Andy Burnham, can't act yet
OL,12,Fbecause he's not even an MP, which is
OL,13,Fwhy his supporters are backing a
OL,14,Fgradual timetable for the PM to go.
OL,15,FAlternatively, a surprise candidate
OL,16,Fcould decide to force matters to a
OL,17,Fhead.
OL,19,FWhoever does move needs to secure the
OL,20,Fsupport of 20% of the Parliamentary
OL,21,FParty - 81 MPs to trigger a contest.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
